waht is github actions: 
GitHub Actions is a continuous integration and continuous delivery (CI/CD) platform that allows you to automate your build, test, and deployment pipeline. 
You can create workflows that build and test every pull request to your repository, or deploy merged pull requests to production.

benifit of github:
# no need of external tool.
# Automate tasks like building, testing, and deploying code, saving time and effort.

components of GitHub Actions:
workflow: collection of jobs,defined in a YAML file.
name : 
Event: any activity in the repo that can trigger a workflow 
ON:
Jobs: collection of steps 
steps: actions to be taken, command,scripts 
Actions:An action is a custom application for the GitHub Actions platform that performs a complex but frequently repeated task.
Runners: A runner is a server that runs your workflows when theyâ€™re triggered. Each runner can run a single job at a time.

How to create workflow:
in git repository click actions and selecte set up a workflow yourself. it will create /.github/workflows/main.yaml(main.yaml our wish we can mention whatever name) there will
